## ğŸ§¹ Data Cleaning & Preparation
The following steps were performed in Excel:

- Converted raw data into structured Excel Tables
- Standardized date and currency formats
- Identified and handled negative or invalid final amounts
- Validated total amounts using quantity Ã— unit price
- Removed duplicate records
- Created time-based fields (Year, Month, Year-Month) for trend analysis

---

## ğŸ“ˆ Dashboard Features
The Excel dashboard includes:

### Key KPIs
- Total Revenue  
- Total Transactions  
- Average Transaction Value  
- Total Discounts Given  

### Visualizations
- Revenue by Store (Column Chart)
- Monthly Revenue Trend (Line Chart)
- Top Aisles by Revenue (Bar Chart)
- Discount vs Final Revenue (Donut Chart)

### Interactivity
- Store slicer
- Year slicer
- Aisle slicer  

These filters allow users to dynamically explore performance across stores, time periods, and product categories.

